###############################################################################
# config_recorder.tf.example
#
# AWS Config rules require a Configuration Recorder + Delivery Channel to
# already exist in the account+region. Most organizations enable this ONCE,
# often at the AWS Organization level via Control Tower / Security Hub, so
# it's intentionally NOT included in the active Terraform config (to avoid
# conflicting with an existing recorder, which causes an apply-time error).
#
# If you do NOT already have AWS Config enabled in this account+region,
# rename this file to config_recorder.tf and run `terraform apply` to
# enable it as part of this stack.
###############################################################################

